	<h2>Installations and Exhibits</h2>
	<h3>Building with Memory</h3>
	<p>
		Building with a Memory is an interactive installation that captures and represents human movement in a collaborative, multi-use workplace. The installation integrates co-located and distributed sensing and feedback, and displays activity over varying scales of time and space. Recording, analyzing and representing the ebb and flow of activity over time provides opportunities for communal reflection and contemplation of group action.
	
